                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/445</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-03T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 29, 9 a.m. Department does not understand from telegram whether you
                    regard Tinoco’s departure as more probable or as less probable in view of
                    strengthened feeling arising from declaration of war.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
